Leke Baiyewu, Abuja The House of Representatives has said it will ensure proper monitoring of the special national security fund when it is created. Chairman of the House Committee on Defence, Mr Babajimi Benson, said his committee would work to ensure accountability and prudence in government spending on security. He also assured all security agencies of his committeeâ€™s readiness to work with them and support them. Benson stated that it had become necessary because of the enormous tasks before both his committee and the security agencies under him. Copyright PUNCH.
